<p class="title"><b>What's next?</b></p>
<p class="instructions-text">By clicking "<b>Download</b>," you'll get our official app installer to automatically download <b>Naukri.com</b>.</p>
</div>
<div class="faq-container">
<details class="main-section">
<summary onclick="addEventAnalytics('instructions_how_to_install_opened', {'event_category': 'instructions'});">
<span>How to install this app on your Android device</span>
<span class="arrow"><img alt="Ver más" width="12" height="12" src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/icons-nolazy.svg#icon-bar-arrow"></span>
</summary>
<div class="sub-items">
<details>
<summary onclick="addEventAnalytics('instructions_xapk_store_opened', {'event_category': 'instructions'});">
<span class="badge">XAPK</span>
<span>XAPK - Installation using the Uptodown app</span>
<span class="arrow"><img alt="Ver más" width="12" height="12" src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/icons-nolazy.svg#icon-bar-arrow"></span>
</summary>
<div class="content">
<div class="info-box">
ℹ️ By default, we distribute XAPK files bundled with our official Android app to ensure proper installation, since Android does not recognize this format on its own. </div>
<p><strong>1-</strong> Tap <i>Download</i> to get the XAPK file.</p>
<p><strong>2-</strong> Once downloaded, locate it in your notification bar or <i>Downloads</i> folder, then tap to begin installation.</p>
<p><strong>3-</strong> If this is your first time using Uptodown, you may see a message asking you to enable installs from unknown sources for our official app. To do this, tap <i>Settings</i> in the pop-up and turn on <i>Grant permission</i>.</p>
<img src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/app/install-guide/native-xapk-install-2.png" alt="Enable unknown sources in the Uptodown app" class="step-image">
<p><strong>4-</strong> After our official app is installed, follow the on-screen instructions to complete the installation of the desired app.</p>
</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary onclick="addEventAnalytics('instructions_xapk_manual_opened', {'event_category': 'instructions'});">
<span class="badge">XAPK</span>
<span>XAPK - Manual installation</span>
<span class="arrow"><img alt="Ver más" width="12" height="12" src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/icons-nolazy.svg#icon-bar-arrow"></span>
</summary>
<div class="content">
<div class="info-box">
ℹ️ Keep in mind that Android cannot install XAPK files by default. You'll need a package installer that supports them. If you prefer not to use our official app, we also offer <a href="https://uptodown-apk-installer.en.uptodown.com/android">APK Installer</a>, our universal installation tool. </div>
<p><strong>1-</strong> To download the XAPK file separately, tap <i>All variants</i> located under the <i>Download</i> button.</p>
<p><strong>2-</strong> Choose the version you want and tap to download the XAPK file.</p>
<p><strong>3-</strong> Locate it in your notification bar or in the <i>Downloads</i> folder, then tap to begin installation.</p>
<p><strong>4-</strong> When opening it, choose a package installer and follow the on-screen instructions. Note: You can also unzip the XAPK and manually move the APK and OBB files into your device's file structure, but we don't recommend this process.</p>
</div>
</details>
</div>
</details>
<details class="main-section">
<summary onclick="addEventAnalytics('instructions_faq_opened', {'event_category': 'instructions'});">
<span>Frequently asked questions</span>
<span class="arrow"><img alt="Ver más" width="12" height="12" src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/icons-nolazy.svg#icon-bar-arrow"></span>
</summary>
<div class="sub-items">
<details>
<summary onclick="addEventAnalytics('instructions_cant_install_opened', {'event_category': 'instructions'});">
<span class="badge badge-problem"></span>
<span>I can't install the app.</span>
<span class="arrow"><img alt="Ver más" width="12" height="12" src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/icons-nolazy.svg#icon-bar-arrow"></span>
</summary>
<div class="content">
<ul>
<li><b>Unknown sources not enabled</b>: Allow installation from unknown sources for your browser or the official Uptodown app (depending on where you're downloading) in <i>Settings > Apps</i>. For more details, visit our <a href="https://support.uptodown.com/hc/articles/4405384237453">Help Center</a>.</li>
</ul>
<img src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/app/install-guide/cant-install-app-2.png" alt="Enable permissions in the Uptodown app" class="step-image">
<ul>
<li><b>Minimum Android version not supported</b>: Make sure your device meets the minimum Android version listed under <i>Requirements</i> on the download page. Also, check compatibility with the file's architecture under <i>Architecture</i> in the app info.</li>
<li><b>Not enough storage space</b>: Free up space by removing apps or files you don't need. If downloaded via a browser, the APK/XAPK file remains on your device, so you'll need at least twice the installer's file size in free space.</li>
<li><b>Corrupt or incomplete file</b>: If your connection is unstable or slow, the file may not download completely. If the installation fails, try downloading it again.</li>
<li><b>Version conflict</b>: If you already have the app installed from another source with a different signature, uninstall it before installing from Uptodown.</li>
<li><b>Installer permissions</b>: Ensure the app you're using to install (browser, file manager, or Uptodown App Store) has permission to install apps.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
<details>
<summary onclick="addEventAnalytics('instructions_does_not_work_opened', {'event_category': 'instructions'});">
<span class="badge badge-problem"></span>
<span>The app installs but doesn't work.</span>
<span class="arrow"><img alt="Ver más" width="12" height="12" src="https://stc.utdstc.com/img/icons-nolazy.svg#icon-bar-arrow"></span>
</summary>
<div class="content">
<ul>
<li><b>Minimum requirements not met</b>: Sometimes apps install even if requirements aren't met, but they may not function properly. Verify that your device meets the RAM, processor, and Android version requirements listed in the technical sheet on Uptodown.</li>
<li><b>Discontinued app</b>: Some apps remain available on Uptodown even if their developers no longer maintain them. Apps with online features may not work. Check the publish date of the latest file or visit the developer's official page.</li>
<li><b>Architecture incompatibility</b>: Some apps require specific architectures (e.g., ARM, ARM64, x86). Check under <i>Older versions</i> to see if one is compatible with your device.</li>
<li><b>Corrupt data or cache</b>: If locally saved app data causes issues, go to <i>Settings > Apps</i>, select the app, and clear cache and data. Back up any important information first.</li>
<li><b>Outdated version</b>: If you installed an older version, the app may require an update. Check Uptodown to confirm you have the latest release.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
</div>
</details>
</div>
